# Cursor Rules for Joel's Personal Website

## Project Context
This is a static personal website for Joel Lopez, an 8th grade student. The site is built with pure HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript - no build tools or frameworks.

## Tech Stack
- HTML5 (semantic HTML)
- CSS3 (vanilla CSS, no preprocessors)
- Vanilla JavaScript (no frameworks)
- Reference design: ./ref/html5up-ethereal/* for look and feel

## Code Style
- Use semantic HTML: header, main, section, footer, nav
- Keep CSS in styles.css, JavaScript in script.js
- Write clear, well-commented code that an 8th grader can understand
- Use consistent spacing and white space
- Follow responsive design principles (mobile-first approach)

## Design Guidelines
- Color scheme: Light background with dark text, black and gold accents (High Tech High colors)
- Typography: Clean sans serif font stack (system UI fonts)
- Layout: Responsive for desktop, tablet, and phone
- Components: Simple cards with rounded corners and subtle shadows
- Interactions: Smooth scrolling, hover animations on buttons and cards

## File Structure
- index.html: Main HTML file
- styles.css: All CSS styles
- script.js: All JavaScript functionality

## Testing
- Use Playwright for UI tests
- Test responsive design on multiple viewport sizes
- Test smooth scrolling and navigation
- Test accessibility and contrast

## Best Practices
- Keep code simple and readable
- No external libraries except Google Fonts if needed
- Ensure good contrast for accessibility
- Use semantic HTML for SEO and accessibility
- Comment code to help Joel understand it

